1_3	0.12729421	Acupuncture, the 5,000-year-old Chinese healing practice, is used in the United States not only for preventing and treating diseases, relieving pain and anesthetizing patients for surgery, but also for face-lifts.
1_4	0.12207324	Acupuncture has been used to improve appearance for at least two decades in this country, for patients who do not want to undergo surgery.
1_5	0.07437391	But only some acupuncturists will do this.
1_6	0.085816822	Many practitioners find the corrective work less professionally satisfying than treating diseases and other ailments.
1_7	0.087503217	Acupuncture is based on the Chinese philosophy called Dao.
1_8	0.074550519	Dao is believed to be directly related to health and well-being, moderation and harmony in mind and body.
1_9	0.074458859	Practitioners seek to restore this balance through Chi, or Qi, Shen and Jing.
1_10	0.075631253	Chi is said to be the energy found in the heart and lungs, in circulating blood and oxygen.
1_11	0.083637755	The Shen is the soul, manifested in personality, perception and awareness of self.
1_12	0.090535744	The Jing is responsible for growth, development and reproduction.
1_13	0.078056933	According to the philosophy, the acupuncturists' role is to help people balance their life of excesses__stress, vices, bad diet__ to achieve a long, healthy life.
1_14	0.1235689	In an acupuncture face-lift, 36-millimeter needles are inserted into facial muscles.
1_15	0.082127299	These needles are believed to produce tiny electric stimulation in anatomic points bringing the blood to the surface, in this case, the face, for better circulation, said Phyllis M.
1_16	0.080483087	Shapiro, an acupuncturist licensed by New York State.
1_17	0.12290692	In acupuncture, there are about 2,000 spots in the body, or acupoints, used for different treatments.
1_18	0.085112441	The points are connected through 12 main channels, or meridians, according to acupuncturists.
1_19	0.088191445	Acupuncture ``can make the skin look healthier,'' by increasing the blood flow to the tissues, Mitchell said, ``but can't produce drastic changes''.
1_20	0.091067908	Some acupuncturists say it is more stimulating treating patients to restore their health rather than enhance appearance.
1_21	0.1039495	``There's less diagnosis,'' said acupuncturist Craig Mitchell from Pacific Institute of Oriental Medicine in New York.
1_22	0.088431294	``It's not necessary to have a thorough interview'' with the patient if she wants to tone up her face, Mitchell said.
1_23	0.090699454	For him as for other colleagues, using acupuncture as a tool for healing is a more challenging job than making people feel good by ``pumping up'' their faces, said acupuncturist Cameron Bishop of Western Communities Family Practice Association in Florida.
1_24	0.081160506	Face-lifts are ``like washing a car,'' Bishop said.
1_25	0.079445812	``It's boring work.
1_26	0.10751075	Would you rather wash a car or do something more interesting''?
